<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I'm a master smithe (skill about 145) and I think this skill is pretty useless. I have made some plats with it, but usually it isn't worth for trouble, because I can make more money from hunting. This is why smithing sucks:<p>

The raw material are too hard to get (atleast for small and large banded)! For example if you are in Freeport (the best town for smithing) and you want to make some small banded, you have to run to Rivervale (no metal sheets there) to get some small armour molds. It is the same way every where... Every town which sells small molds doesen't sell metal sheets! (you can get small blocks of ore from Steamfonts, but those things weights a ton) *sigh*<p>

Only good thing about smithing is that you can twink your newbie chars pretty decently.<p>

*throws his hammer to a forge and walks away*</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
